    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">431 Stevens Street</name>
                    <name type="place">Camden New Jersey U S
                            America<ptr target="tex.00421_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1881-05-30" rend="right">May 30 '81</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Edward Carpenter,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Yours of May 14 <choice>
                <orig>rec'd</orig><reg>received</reg></choice>, with the &#163;3<ptr target="tex.00421_n2"/>&#8212;Many
                thanks&#8212;I send the three L of G by same mail with this, same
                address&#8212;please notify me soon as they reach you safely&#8212;</p>
            <p>I am much as usual&#8212;Pretty well a good deal of the time&#8212;go down to the
                Staffords' farm often&#8212;was there two weeks of this month&#8212;they are
                well&#8212;have not forgotten you&#8212;Harry still works at telegraphing&#8212;</p>
            <p>I was on in Boston five weeks since&#8212;but I believe I sent you a little printed
                item of my jaunt&#8212;</p>
            <p>I sympathize with you in the loss of the dear mother&#8212;I have drunk of that
                cup&#8212;Commend me faithfully in good wishes to my unmet friends you come
                across&#8212;to Robert Sharkland, whose name I have written as you desired, in the
                Volume&#8212;</p>
            <p>Write to me as often as you can, my dear friend&#8212;&#38; I will try the same to
                you&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
